WEBVTT

00:14.119 --> 00:29.119
<b><font color="#00FFFF">Improved By: Fidel33
Sub Upload Date: December 19, 2015</font></b>

00:30.120 --> 00:32.351
<font color="#D900D9">(PEOPLE SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)</font>

00:41.360 --> 00:43.079
<font color="#808080">STAGE MANAGER:</font>
Okay, stand by, everyone.

00:44.120 --> 00:47.830
<font color="#808080">WOMAN:</font>
Five, four, three, two...

00:49.960 --> 00:53.397
At 52 minutes past the hour
on this Thursday morning, welcome back.

00:53.960 --> 00:56.680
Joining me now is author Bill Bryson.

00:57.240 --> 00:59.277
So, travel writing.

01:01.400 --> 01:02.800
- I'm sorry, is that a question?
- <font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>

01:03.320 --> 01:06.279
Noel Coward once said,
"Why do the wrong people travel,"

01:06.360 --> 01:08.158
"and the right people stay at home?"

01:08.640 --> 01:09.915
<font color="#D900D9">(BRYSON SCOFFS)</font>

01:10.000 --> 01:13.391
Now, tell us about this
Collector's Edition Box Set.

01:13.920 --> 01:16.958
"An elegant reissue of old favorites."
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>

01:17.720 --> 01:18.870
Riveting stuff.

01:19.360 --> 01:23.798
Now, in your books, you've written
about Europe, Australia, the British Isles.

01:24.040 --> 01:25.474
You actually lived there briefly.

01:25.840 --> 01:27.320
Briefly. 10 years.

01:27.680 --> 01:28.830
Mmm, but never America.

01:29.320 --> 01:31.357
You've never written
about your home country.

01:31.440 --> 01:34.990
- No, that's not exactly right...
- Why? Why nothing more personal?

01:37.040 --> 01:40.795
I see. So you've moved back,
or is that just temporary?

01:41.360 --> 01:46.355
No. Yes. <font color="#D900D9">(STAMMERING)</font> My family,
we moved back. To New Hampshire.

01:47.720 --> 01:51.430
Twenty years ago. And...
And we're still here.

01:51.720 --> 01:54.758
"Still"? Interesting choice of words.

01:55.800 --> 01:58.110
Uh, what else are you working on?
Are you writing something new?

01:58.200 --> 01:59.270
No.

01:59.440 --> 02:01.272
Not thinking of retiring on us, are you?

02:01.600 --> 02:02.954
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLING)</font>
No, writers don't retire.

02:03.040 --> 02:06.033
We either drink ourselves to death
or blow our brains out.

02:06.760 --> 02:07.955
And which will it be for you?

02:08.479 --> 02:10.152
After this interview, maybe both.

02:10.639 --> 02:11.630
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>

02:11.720 --> 02:14.872
- Bill Bryson, pleasure to have you with us.
- Ah. Thank you.

02:33.000 --> 02:34.912
<font color="#D900D9">(VIDEO GAME PLAYING)</font>

02:38.920 --> 02:40.274
<font color="#808080">CHILD:</font> Oh!
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHING)

02:40.840 --> 02:42.718
<font color="#D900D9">(VACUUM WHIRRING)</font>

02:45.760 --> 02:48.673
- Oh. Hello, stranger.
- <font color="#808080">BRYSON:</font> Hello, yourself.

02:49.240 --> 02:50.435
How'd it go?

02:50.840 --> 02:51.910
- You saw?
- Mmm-hmm.

02:53.400 --> 02:54.834
- That good, huh?
- Hey, Gramps.

02:55.120 --> 02:57.032
- Hi.
- I saw, too.

02:57.280 --> 02:59.272
- Oh, yeah? How'd I look?
- Do you want my honest answer?

03:00.240 --> 03:01.390
Never mind.

03:01.680 --> 03:05.117
- Gramps, I made it to level six.
- Level six? Way to go.

03:05.280 --> 03:06.839
Did you get my message
about Earl McGregor?

03:07.240 --> 03:08.754
Services are on Saturday morning.

03:08.880 --> 03:09.996
Can't we just send flowers?

03:10.880 --> 03:11.996
We could.

03:12.720 --> 03:16.680
You two, hands washed,
dinner's nearly ready. Let's go.

03:19.440 --> 03:22.194
<font color="#D900D9">(WHISPERING INDISTINCTLY)</font>

03:32.920 --> 03:34.957
<font color="#D900D9">(BRYSON SIGHING)</font>

03:38.200 --> 03:40.715
Makes you think
about slowing down, doesn't it?

03:46.600 --> 03:48.796
I'm so, so sorry.
My condolences.

03:49.680 --> 03:52.275
Deborah, we're so sorry.

03:52.360 --> 03:55.910
Thank you so much for being here.
It really means a lot to me.

03:56.960 --> 03:58.030
It's our pleasure.

04:01.160 --> 04:03.231
Uh, I mean, not our...
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY)</font> Pardon me.

04:03.320 --> 04:06.677
Uh, I mean, it's, uh, not a pleasant time,

04:07.760 --> 04:10.673
- and it's not a time...
- No, we're just very sorry.

04:11.080 --> 04:12.753
- We're very sorry.
- We're very sorry.

04:17.079 --> 04:19.470
- I'll get my jacket.
- We just got here.

04:20.560 --> 04:23.359
What? We've already paid our respects.
I mean, what else are we supposed to do?

04:23.440 --> 04:25.671
Talk to people. It's good for you.

04:26.920 --> 04:28.718
I don't like talking to people.

04:29.680 --> 04:30.670
Go on.

04:31.680 --> 04:33.751
- How are you? How good to see you.
- <font color="#D900D9">(SIGHING)</font>

04:52.640 --> 04:54.040
I'm gonna go for a walk.

04:54.520 --> 04:55.556
Okay.

05:08.480 --> 05:10.073
<font color="#D900D9">(CLEARS THROAT)</font>

05:54.720 --> 05:56.200
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)</font>

06:15.240 --> 06:16.833
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>

06:20.440 --> 06:22.397
<font color="#D900D9">(FAINT HAMMERING)</font>

06:29.320 --> 06:30.515
<font color="#808080">CATHERINE:</font> What on earth?

06:32.680 --> 06:34.558
- You want to hike it?
- Yes.

06:35.320 --> 06:36.470
<font color="#808080">CATHERINE:</font>
Two thousand miles.

06:36.600 --> 06:38.876
2118, actually.

06:39.480 --> 06:41.517
No. You can't.

06:43.520 --> 06:44.715
Why not?

06:44.880 --> 06:48.510
Seriously, Bill.
Even for you this is ridiculous.

06:48.920 --> 06:50.912
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLING)</font> Why?
Because you think I'm too old?

06:51.000 --> 06:53.834
No, it's not because I think you're too
old, it's because you are too old.

06:54.920 --> 06:56.320
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>

06:56.800 --> 06:58.632
Oh, God, is this because of the funeral?

06:58.960 --> 07:00.440
- No.
- What then?

07:01.440 --> 07:02.476
Listen, I can't explain it.

07:03.160 --> 07:04.230
Have a go.

07:05.200 --> 07:07.317
It's just something I feel I have to do.

07:08.240 --> 07:11.199
I want to explore nature.
I want to get back to my roots.

07:12.400 --> 07:15.313
- Roots?
- Yeah. You know, push myself.

07:15.640 --> 07:17.233
I mean, really, really hike.

07:17.560 --> 07:18.596
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>

07:18.680 --> 07:22.515
Hike? You haven't hiked in 30 years.

07:23.000 --> 07:25.196
- <font color="#808080">BRYSON:</font> Exactly.
- Can't you just do this in the Volvo?

07:25.440 --> 07:26.510
Catherine.

07:27.880 --> 07:29.280
What if I say you can't go?

07:29.680 --> 07:32.752
Well, if you felt that way
then we would discuss it.

07:32.960 --> 07:35.794
You mean I'll yammer on
and you'll nod away,

07:35.880 --> 07:38.600
and then you'll go ahead and do whatever
you were going to do anyway

07:38.680 --> 07:40.353
without having heard a word I've said.

07:41.320 --> 07:42.515
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHING)</font>

07:42.600 --> 07:44.398
- What?
- <font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLING)</font>

07:44.480 --> 07:45.914
Am I just supposed to stand here

07:46.000 --> 07:48.959
and accept these obvious signs
that you have gone mad?

07:49.920 --> 07:52.230
It's my old pup tent. What do you think?

07:55.040 --> 07:57.680
Well, I think it's the perfect place
for you to spend the night.

08:00.440 --> 08:03.512
<font color="#808080">SAM:</font> You realize we all think
this is a terrible idea, right?

08:03.600 --> 08:05.114
<font color="#808080">BRYSON:</font> It's certainly been brought
to my attention.

08:05.200 --> 08:07.271
- <font color="#808080">SAM:</font> But you're still going to do it?
- Yes.

08:08.360 --> 08:10.033
<font color="#D900D9">(SAM CHUCKLING)</font>

08:10.440 --> 08:14.229
It's just kinda insane, Dad.
The whole thing, at your age?

08:14.760 --> 08:17.195
Fit people in their 20's can't do it, Dad.

08:17.280 --> 08:19.431
It takes five months and
five millions steps.

08:19.720 --> 08:20.790
- Of walking.
- Yes.

08:20.880 --> 08:22.360
I've been doing it for a while, you know.

08:22.920 --> 08:24.479
Dad, hiking is not walking.

08:24.560 --> 08:27.519
Two thousand people a year try to do this.
Less than 10% make it.

08:28.040 --> 08:31.158
You ought to see the statistics
on how many people finish writing a book.

08:31.280 --> 08:33.794
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font> There's somebody
I want you to meet. All right?

08:34.039 --> 08:35.235
Hey, Dave.

08:35.960 --> 08:36.996
How's it going?

08:37.120 --> 08:38.155
This is Dave.

08:38.360 --> 08:39.395
- Dave.
- Hello.

08:39.480 --> 08:41.198
He has hiked everywhere.

08:41.280 --> 08:43.510
He can answer any question
you have about anything.

08:44.280 --> 08:47.114
Okay. Can he tell me
why the caged bird sings?

08:48.760 --> 08:51.753
Can you give us just a second? And can I?

08:54.040 --> 08:56.635
Can we keep a lid on the jokes, please?

08:57.080 --> 08:59.151
Pay attention while he's talking,

08:59.280 --> 09:00.873
and don't say,
"You've got to be shitting me"

09:00.960 --> 09:02.110
when he tells you the price of something.

09:02.200 --> 09:05.034
Sam, you act like I've never camped before.

09:05.280 --> 09:06.475
A tent is a tent.

09:07.080 --> 09:11.677
This also has a 70 denier,
high-density, abrasion-resistant fly

09:11.760 --> 09:13.319
with that same rip stop weave.

09:14.040 --> 09:15.394
And just look at these seams.

09:16.320 --> 09:19.518
All lap-felled.
No bias taping on the whole tent.

09:19.800 --> 09:23.794
And the poles. Color-coded, DAC aluminum.

09:24.440 --> 09:26.432
It's the finest craftsmanship.

09:27.040 --> 09:31.637
Yeah, I've carried this one
on several sections of the trail myself.

09:32.880 --> 09:36.271
For your purposes,
cannot go wrong with this monster.

09:37.600 --> 09:38.829
All right, how much is it?

09:38.920 --> 09:41.355
This one here is 289.

09:42.120 --> 09:45.272
You've got to be shitting... Oh, okay.

09:45.560 --> 09:49.031
I see what you're thinking, but out
on the trail, you're gonna thank me.

09:49.240 --> 09:50.435
Are you coming?

09:51.200 --> 09:52.953
You'll need a rain cover too, of course.

09:53.040 --> 09:55.714
- A rain cover? Why?
- To keep out the rain.

09:55.800 --> 09:58.998
- The backpacks aren't waterproof?
- Not 100%.

09:59.240 --> 10:02.278
The rain cover weighs
four point six ounces.

10:02.360 --> 10:05.671
You know how much weight it would add
to fully waterproof an 85-liter pack?

10:06.480 --> 10:08.631
Well, I'll tell you. <font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font> It's a lot.

10:09.680 --> 10:11.353
Let's not forget...

10:12.480 --> 10:15.518
Oh, let me guess, in case you want
to do a little impromptu gardening?

10:15.640 --> 10:19.270
No. You know the saying, "Take only
memories, leave only footprints".

10:21.920 --> 10:23.036
Poop.

10:23.560 --> 10:25.199
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHS)</font>

10:25.520 --> 10:27.671
- Oh, shit.
- Exactly.

10:43.160 --> 10:45.755
<font color="#808080">CATHERINE:</font>
Thought you'd find these interesting.

10:46.680 --> 10:51.277
A Virginia man's remains
left undiscovered for 18 days

10:51.360 --> 10:54.159
after he suffers
a catastrophic medical condition

10:54.240 --> 10:56.675
just one week into his solo trek.

10:57.400 --> 11:02.634
Most commonly spread through
infected rodent saliva, urine, and feces,

11:02.760 --> 11:04.433
which become airborne particles...

11:04.760 --> 11:08.595
Several law enforcement personnel
have expressed concern

11:08.680 --> 11:11.320
about the gruesome nature
of these latest murders,

11:11.440 --> 11:14.399
including dismemberment
and ritualistic savagery.

11:15.240 --> 11:17.550
You are not doing this alone.

11:17.800 --> 11:18.916
<font color="#808080">BRYSON:</font> This is Bryson.

11:19.760 --> 11:23.151
How would you like to join me
for a little stroll?

11:23.560 --> 11:27.076
It's a chance to grab some fresh air,
while there's still some left.

11:27.760 --> 11:30.878
You know, studies show
Americans need to walk more.

11:31.360 --> 11:33.238
Our forefathers, they walked everywhere.

11:33.640 --> 11:35.757
It'll give you something to do
for the next six months.

11:36.840 --> 11:38.638
Let me know if you're interested.

11:40.080 --> 11:42.356
<font color="#808080">CATHERINE:</font> Rabies, crazed skunks,
raccoons, and squirrels,

11:42.440 --> 11:44.557
merciless fire ants, and ravening blackfly.

11:44.680 --> 11:46.672
Poison ivy, poison sumac, poison oak,

11:46.760 --> 11:48.399
poison salamanders,
even a scattering of moose?

11:48.520 --> 11:49.510
<font color="#D900D9">(PHONE BEEPS)</font>

11:49.600 --> 11:51.876
<font color="#808080">MAN #1:</font> Bryson, four words:
Not in this lifetime.

11:51.960 --> 11:52.996
<font color="#D900D9">(BEEPS)</font>

11:53.080 --> 11:55.800
<font color="#808080">MAN #2:</font> I wish I could, Bill,
but I just switched to a new beta blocker.

11:55.880 --> 11:56.870
I barely have enough energy

11:56.960 --> 11:57.996
- to get dressed in the...
- <font color="#D900D9">(BEEPS)</font>

11:58.080 --> 11:59.958
<font color="#808080">MAN #3:</font> Next time, call
me for something fun.

12:00.040 --> 12:01.474
- Like a colonoscopy.
- <font color="#D900D9">(BEEPS)</font>

12:01.880 --> 12:03.997
<font color="#808080">MAN #4:</font> Bill, I think you've been the victim
of identity theft.

12:04.080 --> 12:05.480
I got the most ridiculous message

12:05.560 --> 12:06.789
- from someone claiming...
- <font color="#D900D9">(BEEPS)</font>

12:06.880 --> 12:09.952
<font color="#808080">MAN #5:</font> Bill, you know you can see the whole
trail online in less than four minutes?

12:10.560 --> 12:14.679
You know, you can't count Dan Budge.
Dying is not the same as saying no.

12:14.760 --> 12:15.989
<font color="#D900D9">(BRYSON MUMBLES)</font>

12:18.360 --> 12:20.556
Did we know about that?
About Dan's death?

12:21.760 --> 12:24.434
Yeah, I think
it was in Janice's Christmas card.

12:26.360 --> 12:29.398
Well, that explains why she was so miffed
about my invitation.

12:30.000 --> 12:32.151
<font color="#D900D9">(PHONE RINGING)</font>

12:33.120 --> 12:34.156
It's in the...

12:40.400 --> 12:42.312
- <font color="#D900D9">(BEEPS)</font>
- Hello?

12:43.760 --> 12:44.796
Hello?

12:44.920 --> 12:46.479
<font color="#808080">KATZ:</font> Hey, it's me.

12:46.760 --> 12:47.830
I'm sorry?

12:48.480 --> 12:50.472
Bryson, it's Katz.

12:51.320 --> 12:53.152
- It's Katz?
- Yeah.

12:53.360 --> 12:55.238
- Stephen?
- Yeah.

12:55.600 --> 12:57.034
- <font color="#D900D9">(KATZ LAUGHS)</font>
- Whoa.

12:58.200 --> 12:59.520
You're in the States?

13:00.360 --> 13:01.953
Yeah, yeah. Where are you?

13:02.200 --> 13:05.876
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font> I'm in Des Moines.
Where the hell else would I be?

13:06.760 --> 13:08.672
Well, it's good to hear your voice.

13:08.960 --> 13:13.273
Yeah. Hey, Doug told me about
this Appalachian Trail deal of yours.

13:13.520 --> 13:14.840
Are you serious about that?

13:15.360 --> 13:17.158
Yes, I'm very serious.

13:18.400 --> 13:20.710
You think maybe I could come with you?

13:22.560 --> 13:25.280
<font color="#D900D9">(STAMMERS)</font>
You wanna come with me?

13:25.920 --> 13:28.833
Yeah, if it's a problem, I understand.

13:28.920 --> 13:33.836
- No, no, no, no.
- I mean, I understand if you don't want me.

13:34.240 --> 13:36.232
No, why... Why wouldn't I want you?

13:36.960 --> 13:40.510
Because, you know,
I still owe you 600 bucks from Europe.

13:41.000 --> 13:43.390
Well, that was forty years ago, Stephen.

13:43.680 --> 13:46.559
Yeah, but I still intend to pay you.

13:47.200 --> 13:48.554
Well, I know you're good for it.

13:48.680 --> 13:50.160
Ah, great, great.

13:50.520 --> 13:52.398
<font color="#808080">BRYSON:</font> So, what kind
of shape you in?

13:52.600 --> 13:56.230
Well, I'm in good shape.
I walk everywhere these days.

13:56.400 --> 13:57.470
Really?

13:57.560 --> 14:00.155
Yeah, since the bastards
took away my license.

14:00.240 --> 14:01.594
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>

14:02.440 --> 14:03.669
Um...

14:04.200 --> 14:05.953
So, how are you with bears?

14:06.560 --> 14:09.871
Well, they haven't gotten me yet.
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHS)</font>

14:10.280 --> 14:14.513
Well, you know there can't be a black bear
within 1,500 miles of Des Moines, Katz.

14:14.600 --> 14:18.833
That's what I'm saying, man.
Those fuckers keep their distance.

14:19.080 --> 14:21.231
<font color="#D900D9">(BOTH LAUGHING)</font>

14:22.280 --> 14:24.033
You'll never guess who just gave me a call.

14:24.120 --> 14:26.476
No, no, no. Not Stephen Katz.

14:27.320 --> 14:28.515
Mmm-mmm.

14:28.600 --> 14:30.512
You said I couldn't go alone.

14:30.680 --> 14:33.912
Well, presuming you were going
to get somebody responsible.

14:34.440 --> 14:35.510
You don't even know him.

14:35.600 --> 14:37.956
Well, I know the stories.
Didn't he have a drinking problem?

14:38.080 --> 14:39.116
We all had drinking problems.

14:39.200 --> 14:41.032
Well, you two ended up
on each other's nerves in Europe.

14:41.120 --> 14:43.794
No, no, no, no.
We started out on each other's nerves.

14:44.480 --> 14:45.960
We ended up despising each other.

14:46.200 --> 14:47.600
<font color="#D900D9">(SCOFFS)</font>

14:48.560 --> 14:50.552
You know I hate this, right?

14:50.760 --> 14:53.594
Sweetheart, I really don't think
you have anything to worry about.

14:53.800 --> 14:56.235
No. Just my husband wandering off
into the woods,

14:56.320 --> 14:58.516
surely to be maimed or killed

14:58.680 --> 15:01.832
or contract some ghastly
parasitic disease which,

15:01.960 --> 15:05.317
if lucky, will leave him propped up
in a chair, drooling into his own bib.

15:05.560 --> 15:07.119
But there's nothing to worry about,
because of course

15:07.200 --> 15:10.352
I'll be the one expected to stand
by your side, feeding you ice chips

15:10.440 --> 15:14.639
until you capitulate to this
unnamed malady, and then what?

15:15.800 --> 15:18.395
I get to stand in front
of some gaudy church saying,

15:18.520 --> 15:20.876
"He was a loving husband and father,"

15:21.640 --> 15:24.075
"once considered to be
a man of reasonable intelligence,"

15:24.160 --> 15:25.879
"since revealed to be nothing more"

15:26.680 --> 15:28.637
"than a daft and utter fool."

15:28.720 --> 15:30.552
Well, it's a shame I won't
be there to hear it.

15:33.200 --> 15:35.351
Look, I know what this seems like, okay?

15:35.480 --> 15:37.472
Have you actually
thought this through at all?

15:38.520 --> 15:39.715
Of course not.

15:49.360 --> 15:52.876
<font color="#808080">WOMAN:</font> <font color="#D900D9">(ON P.A)</font> Lebanon Airport
welcomes Cape Air Flight 106.

15:53.000 --> 15:54.912
Travelers arriving from Springfield

15:55.000 --> 15:57.834
can claim their baggage
at Baggage Claim Carousel Four.

16:02.360 --> 16:03.430
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTS)</font>

16:10.480 --> 16:11.550
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTS)</font>

16:15.760 --> 16:17.194
You are shitting me.

16:18.400 --> 16:19.720
<font color="#D900D9">(BRYSON CHUCKLES)</font>

16:25.240 --> 16:26.913
- Hey, Stephen.
- Bryson.

16:28.400 --> 16:29.720
How are you?

16:32.080 --> 16:33.309
Hello, Steve-o.

16:33.400 --> 16:34.550
This is my wife.

16:35.400 --> 16:38.393
You're the British nurse
I've heard so much about.

16:38.800 --> 16:40.280
- I certainly hope so.
- Yeah.

16:40.600 --> 16:41.750
Good to meet you.

16:43.400 --> 16:45.232
That's a little bit like a bear hug.

16:45.760 --> 16:46.750
Are you limping?

16:47.640 --> 16:51.919
