35:22.480 --> 35:24.836
- And you? You're a Libra.
- <font color="#D900D9">(SCOFFS)</font>

35:25.040 --> 35:27.714
Definitely a Libra.
I could make a living doing this.

35:28.240 --> 35:30.880
You're zero for two, honey. Zero for two.

35:31.040 --> 35:32.554
Can you guys guess what I am?

35:32.760 --> 35:34.717
- Couple of thoughts come to mind.
- Yeah?

35:35.400 --> 35:37.392
<font color="#808080">MARY ELLEN:</font> <font color="#D900D9">(SINGING)</font>
She's up all night to the sun.

35:37.480 --> 35:39.551
I'm up all night to get some.

35:39.640 --> 35:41.632
She's up all night for good fun.

35:41.720 --> 35:43.234
We're up all night to get lucky

35:44.040 --> 35:46.271
<font color="#D900D9">(CONTINUES SINGING)</font>

35:46.920 --> 35:48.070
<font color="#808080">KATZ:</font> Fuck.

35:50.880 --> 35:52.837
God damn it. Damn it!

35:53.320 --> 35:55.039
<font color="#D900D9">(GROANING)</font>

35:57.200 --> 35:58.475
<font color="#D900D9">(UNZIPPING)</font>

35:59.640 --> 36:02.474
I swear to God I'm gonna
rip her larynx out.

36:03.880 --> 36:06.839
I'm not sure that's going to do it.
I got a better plan.

36:07.000 --> 36:08.229
Go on, lay it on me.

36:08.320 --> 36:11.552
Okay, according to the map,
we get to Hiawassee tomorrow.

36:11.880 --> 36:15.430
We get an early start and we hike hard,
we can put some distance between us.

36:16.080 --> 36:17.719
Yeah, that's probably better than my plan.

36:18.040 --> 36:19.076
What's your plan?

36:19.280 --> 36:21.112
Kill her. Take her Pop-tarts.

36:27.720 --> 36:29.712
- Hey, good morning.
- <font color="#808080">BOTH:</font> Good morning.

36:31.600 --> 36:32.590
You guys heading out?

36:33.400 --> 36:35.278
Yeah. You want us to wait for you?

36:35.440 --> 36:36.430
Yeah, we'll wait.

36:36.960 --> 36:39.429
Nah, I'll catch up. I'm pretty regular.

36:44.760 --> 36:45.876
<font color="#D900D9">(WHISPERS)</font> We go.

37:30.160 --> 37:31.674
<font color="#808080">BRYSON:</font> We've still got
a couple more miles.

37:31.880 --> 37:33.030
How far back is she?

37:34.320 --> 37:35.515
She's gaining.

37:35.600 --> 37:37.239
- I don't think...
- I don't... <font color="#D900D9">(YELPS)</font>

37:38.160 --> 37:39.230
We need a new plan.

37:39.680 --> 37:41.637
- Yeah, we do. We need a new plan.
- Yeah.

37:44.560 --> 37:46.597
<font color="#D900D9">(PANTING)</font>

37:48.520 --> 37:49.556
Shh.

37:49.640 --> 37:51.154
I didn't say anything.

37:51.480 --> 37:54.040
- Well, you sound like a DC-10. Keep it down.
- Oh.

37:54.560 --> 37:56.040
- <font color="#D900D9">(PANTING)</font>
- <font color="#D900D9">(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)</font>

37:56.120 --> 37:57.190
Here she comes.

38:00.400 --> 38:02.198
<font color="#D900D9">(KATZ WHEEZING)</font>

38:03.200 --> 38:04.520
- Hold your breath.
- <font color="#D900D9">(GASPS)</font>

38:15.800 --> 38:16.836
<font color="#D900D9">(WHISPERS)</font>
Hold it, hold it.

38:20.200 --> 38:21.190
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

38:23.440 --> 38:28.879
<font color="#D900D9">(SINGING)</font> We've come
too far to give up who we are

38:31.880 --> 38:33.155
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTS)</font>

38:33.400 --> 38:34.470
We go, we go!

38:40.480 --> 38:43.439
- Hey, hey, hey! Hey!
- Hey!

38:43.720 --> 38:45.552
Wait, stop!

38:48.080 --> 38:50.515
Who the hell's gonna stop for us?
We look like shit.

38:52.360 --> 38:54.238
<font color="#808080">KATZ:</font> Hey, stop!

38:56.600 --> 38:58.080
<font color="#D900D9">(TYRES SCREECHING)</font>

38:58.680 --> 38:59.750
They stopped!

39:00.240 --> 39:01.879
<font color="#D900D9">(ROCK MUSIC PLAYING ON STEREO)</font>

39:01.960 --> 39:03.030
<font color="#D900D9">(TYRES SCREECH)</font>

39:03.680 --> 39:05.194
Hey, you boys want a ride?

39:05.720 --> 39:06.870
Sure do!

39:12.680 --> 39:14.433
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHS)</font>

39:15.400 --> 39:17.756
Y'all have to excuse us.
We are celebrating.

39:18.120 --> 39:20.032
Yeah? What are you celebrating?

39:20.400 --> 39:22.392
We are getting married tomorrow.

39:22.880 --> 39:25.475
- Great, great.
- Congratulations, you guys.

39:26.120 --> 39:27.918
Yeah, Darren is making
an honest woman out of me.

39:28.000 --> 39:29.354
- Ain't that right, baby?
- Yes, I am.

39:31.000 --> 39:32.514
- Uh, you wanna watch the...
- <font color="#D900D9">(TYRES SCREECH)</font>

39:32.640 --> 39:33.630
<font color="#D900D9">(DONNA SQUEALS)</font>

39:37.680 --> 39:39.114
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHS)</font>

39:39.640 --> 39:41.233
<font color="#D900D9">(UNHOOKING BELT)</font>

39:43.760 --> 39:44.750
<font color="#808080">DARREN:</font> Yeah.

39:48.400 --> 39:52.314
Holy shit. I wish I was still 20.

39:53.080 --> 39:54.719
I wish I was still 50.

39:56.080 --> 39:57.799
<font color="#808080">DONNA:</font> See y'all later.
<font color="#808080">DARREN:</font> Bye, y'all.

40:06.160 --> 40:07.435
What can I get you boys to drink?

40:07.520 --> 40:10.911
The tallest and the coldest beer
you can offer.

40:12.080 --> 40:13.070
Coke.

40:13.360 --> 40:16.592
- Just Coke, nothing in it?
- Just Coke. I'm reformed.

40:16.760 --> 40:18.672
- Okay.
- Uh, you know what?

40:19.680 --> 40:21.512
Make mine a Coke also.

40:22.000 --> 40:23.639
All right. Just a second.

40:27.480 --> 40:30.632
Oh, wow. I'm... I'm impressed.

40:31.560 --> 40:34.473
Well, you know, ever since
I rolled my car on route six,

40:35.520 --> 40:39.594
- I had to rethink some things.
- Yeah, that'll do it.

40:41.200 --> 40:44.511
A lady cop came up to the window
and she knocked.

40:46.200 --> 40:50.592
I was hanging upside down by the seatbelt
and I said, "What's the problem, officer?"

40:50.760 --> 40:51.796
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>

40:51.880 --> 40:54.190
She just stared at me and walked away.

40:55.320 --> 40:58.233
So I haven't had a drink since.

40:59.240 --> 41:01.596
- Really?
- Yeah.

41:02.920 --> 41:04.195
Well, that's good.

41:06.000 --> 41:08.674
- Good for you.
- Yeah. Good for me.

41:09.320 --> 41:10.356
Really.

41:14.520 --> 41:15.636
Ah.

41:18.520 --> 41:19.590
You know, Bryson,

41:19.720 --> 41:24.715
I keep looking at the door over there and
I keep seeing Mary Ellen coming through.

41:26.760 --> 41:28.274
I hope you're not going to tell me
you miss her?

41:28.600 --> 41:31.479
Oh, no, no. Hell no,
I'm not going to tell you that.

41:31.600 --> 41:34.354
I mean, we did kind of ditch her though,
didn't we?

41:34.440 --> 41:37.035
No, we didn't just kind of ditch her,
Stephen. We ditched her.

41:37.120 --> 41:41.080
Yeah. We left her all alone in the woods
by herself.

41:41.240 --> 41:42.435
She came into the woods by herself.

41:42.560 --> 41:45.200
It's not like we signed a contract
to look after her.

41:45.280 --> 41:48.000
No, but she's probably scared out
of her wits.

41:48.640 --> 41:50.199
What are you so interested in her for?

41:50.320 --> 41:52.789
I'm not interested in her at all.

41:53.600 --> 41:56.911
The damndest thing,
Bryson, is I am a Libra.

41:59.760 --> 42:00.955
She got it right.

42:03.720 --> 42:05.712
Maybe she has a gift.

42:06.680 --> 42:08.000
What are the chances?

42:08.800 --> 42:10.359
One in 12, actually.

42:10.760 --> 42:14.117
One in 12. That's pretty damn good.

42:20.640 --> 42:22.632
Oh. Southbound, coming through.

42:26.480 --> 42:28.995
<font color="#808080">MAN:</font> Mary Ellen?
Oh, yeah, she talked about you guys.

42:29.120 --> 42:30.349
<font color="#808080">KATZ:</font> Yeah? What did she say?

42:31.040 --> 42:32.440
- Well, her words, right?
- <font color="#808080">KATZ:</font> Right.

42:32.640 --> 42:34.791
She said you guys
were a couple of overweight wimps

42:34.920 --> 42:36.434
who didn't know the
first thing about hiking.

42:37.560 --> 42:38.755
And she was tired of carrying you.

42:39.400 --> 42:41.153
Oh, Holy Christ Almighty.

42:41.280 --> 42:43.556
Actually, I think she called you
a couple of pussies.

42:43.840 --> 42:45.194
- Pussies?
- Pussies?

42:46.440 --> 42:47.635
After all we did for her?

42:48.280 --> 42:51.079
You guys know it's supposed to snow
tonight, right? Six to eight inches.

42:51.240 --> 42:52.993
- Really?
- <font color="#808080">MAN:</font> More higher up.

42:53.320 --> 42:56.119
That's what they're saying.
You're going to be climbing right into it.

42:56.320 --> 42:57.470
- Yeah? Oh.
- Yeah.

42:59.960 --> 43:03.237
- Well, I gotta keep moving, guys. Be safe.
- <font color="#808080">BRYSON:</font> Thanks.

43:03.680 --> 43:06.115
<font color="#808080">KATZ:</font> Snow?
That guy's out of his fucking mind.

43:06.680 --> 43:08.672
<font color="#D900D9">(WIND WHOOSHING)</font>

43:20.520 --> 43:22.352
<font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMING)</font>

43:24.360 --> 43:25.396
You okay?

43:25.840 --> 43:27.240
Never better.

43:31.640 --> 43:32.994
Goddamn things are useless.

43:34.880 --> 43:37.440
What I'm thinking
we could do is follow this logging road,

43:38.200 --> 43:40.271
get to the other side of this ridge,
and get out of the wind

43:40.360 --> 43:42.920
where we can set up our camp.
What do you think?

43:43.120 --> 43:47.194
Me? I think I'd rather have a nice hot soak
in a Jacuzzi.

43:47.720 --> 43:51.555
But if you're dead-set on following
that logging road, we can do that, too.

43:52.040 --> 43:56.193
We can save the Jacuzzi for another time
when things aren't going so well.

43:56.360 --> 43:57.476
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLING)</font> Yeah.

43:57.560 --> 43:59.153
- I'll follow you.
- Okay.

44:08.840 --> 44:10.354
Katz, you still there?

44:11.560 --> 44:13.870
- <font color="#808080">KATZ:</font> Unfortunately.
- <font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>

44:28.600 --> 44:30.353
Just like you said, Bryson.

44:31.240 --> 44:35.359
The AT. You never know what lies ahead.

44:36.720 --> 44:37.915
So it appears.

44:59.480 --> 45:02.837
<font color="#808080">WOMAN:</font> I promise you, if there was heat,
it would be on, honey, all right?

45:03.120 --> 45:05.157
Use the talcum powder, that helps.

45:06.280 --> 45:10.399
Hi. We'd like a cabin.
Preferably with a private bath.

45:11.000 --> 45:14.710
The cabins went two days ago.
But I do have two spaces in the bunkhouse.

45:16.640 --> 45:17.790
<font color="#D900D9">(KATZ GRUNTS)</font>

45:19.120 --> 45:21.316
<font color="#808080">KATZ:</font> I don't know
if you're aware of this, Bryson,

45:21.720 --> 45:24.474
but every time I hear the word "bunkhouse"

45:25.240 --> 45:28.199
my testicles shrink up inside my body.

45:39.000 --> 45:40.150
Welcome to the Stalag.

45:40.280 --> 45:42.590
There's a meeting of the Escape Committee
at 1900 hours.

45:42.680 --> 45:43.830
Oh, okay.

45:56.480 --> 45:59.120
Hey, are you liking that XT-85?

46:00.120 --> 46:01.395
Your pack.

46:01.640 --> 46:02.676
Oh.

46:03.280 --> 46:05.112
- I got a Gregory.
- Oh, yeah?

46:05.320 --> 46:07.755
Yeah. I looked at the XT-85, solid pack.

46:07.960 --> 46:09.030
But the quad access points,

46:09.160 --> 46:11.391
dual hydration ports in the Gregory,
they sold me.

46:13.200 --> 46:14.839
What made you buy an XT-85?

46:15.840 --> 46:18.196
I thought it was easier
than carrying everything in my arms.

46:25.960 --> 46:29.317
- How come you're up top?
- Well, heat rises, pal.

46:31.760 --> 46:34.036
<font color="#D900D9">(KATZ GRUNTING)</font>

46:41.720 --> 46:43.040
Oh, yeah.

46:46.320 --> 46:48.630
<font color="#D900D9">(BED CREAKING)</font>

46:48.720 --> 46:50.040
Hey, you know...

46:53.880 --> 46:56.634
<font color="#808080">KATZ:</font> <font color="#D900D9">(GROANS)</font>
Hey, Bryson, are you all right?

46:56.920 --> 46:58.400
<font color="#808080">BRYSON:</font> Oh, never better.

46:59.680 --> 47:02.070
<font color="#D900D9">(MOTIVATIONAL SONG PLAYING)</font>

47:50.040 --> 47:52.794
We can start, maybe, right there and...

47:56.440 --> 47:57.920
Hello, there.

48:00.080 --> 48:01.878
You guys, uh, doing all right?

48:02.760 --> 48:03.955
Yeah, we're fine.

48:04.440 --> 48:05.760
Because, look,
when we get over to the other side,

48:05.840 --> 48:07.957
we can just come back
and grab your packs if you want?

48:09.320 --> 48:10.470
You know, it's easy for us.

48:10.640 --> 48:11.915
- Not a problem.
- Happy to help.

48:12.240 --> 48:15.916
We like hard, we don't like easy.
But thanks a lot, you know.

48:17.480 --> 48:19.392
- All right, then.
- Okay.

48:20.120 --> 48:21.998
- Excuse us. All right.
- Yep.

48:33.560 --> 48:35.313
- Nice guys.
- Yep.

48:35.840 --> 48:37.752
- I hate 'em.
- Me, too.

48:39.440 --> 48:40.430
Well...

48:57.160 --> 48:58.196
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTS)</font>

49:05.080 --> 49:06.116
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTS)</font>

49:06.600 --> 49:07.829
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font>

49:20.960 --> 49:23.680
- That went well.
- It was refreshing.

49:28.000 --> 49:30.356
Bryson, you've got everything
a man could want.

49:31.120 --> 49:34.511
And here you are,
tramping around in the woods with me.

49:35.600 --> 49:36.875
Seriously, what gives?

49:38.240 --> 49:39.833
I don't know.

49:41.880 --> 49:44.600
As John Muir once said,
"Sometimes a man just has to"

49:45.720 --> 49:49.350
"get a loaf of bread and throw it into a
sack, and jump over the back fence."

49:49.720 --> 49:51.552
Oh, I got you.

49:51.840 --> 49:54.400
Life's a little too perfect
inside that fence, huh?

49:54.960 --> 49:57.270
- No, no, no...
- Oh, you made sense, Bryson.

49:57.400 --> 49:58.959
You're a caged animal.

49:59.240 --> 50:02.312
You wanna get back into that forest.
Live a little.

50:03.600 --> 50:06.320
- That's not it.
- No, that's got to be it.

50:07.400 --> 50:08.834
So why'd you come?

50:09.560 --> 50:13.076
<font color="#808080">KATZ:</font> I guess I didn't want to spend
the rest of my life in jail.

50:13.760 --> 50:15.877
- <font color="#808080">BRYSON:</font> What?
- <font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLING)</font> It's nothing, really.

50:16.840 --> 50:21.198
Just a couple of outstanding warrants
I didn't show up for and stuff like that.

50:21.320 --> 50:24.916
Jesus, Stephen, that's really not something
you can run from.

50:25.200 --> 50:26.520
<font color="#D900D9">(KATZ LAUGHS)</font>

50:26.800 --> 50:28.837
<font color="#808080">KATZ:</font> Actually, you kind of can.

50:29.760 --> 50:31.877
<font color="#808080">BRYSON:</font> Same old Stephen.
Always running from something.

50:32.080 --> 50:34.675
<font color="#808080">KATZ:</font> Oh, really?
You're one to talk.

50:35.200 --> 50:36.475
Not you.

50:37.800 --> 50:40.872
Remind me again why we're out here?

50:41.080 --> 50:42.355
It's was not like
you had something better to do.

50:42.440 --> 50:44.955
As I recall, in fact,
you begged me to come.

50:45.120 --> 50:47.954
I begged? I begged to come? I asked.

50:48.920 --> 50:51.037
You know what cracks me up, Bryson?

50:51.640 --> 50:56.476
Is how predictable your whole life
has become, right down to the Volvo.

50:56.560 --> 50:58.392
God forbid somebody should evolve

50:58.520 --> 51:00.273
rather than squandering away
their existence.

51:00.400 --> 51:03.757
I mean, look at you. All these years
and you're still stuck at square one.

51:04.320 --> 51:06.232
Hey, Bryson. Are you happy?

51:06.320 --> 51:07.993
What the hell kind of a question is that?

51:08.160 --> 51:10.311
Pretty important question, I'd say.

51:10.440 --> 51:11.635
What, do you think you're happy?

51:12.080 --> 51:13.355
I think...

51:25.960 --> 51:27.360
Wow.

51:28.840 --> 51:30.320
The Smokies.

51:34.520 --> 51:36.432
<font color="#808080">BRYSON:</font> Now this is interesting.

51:39.200 --> 51:40.759
Oh, God, this is amazing.

51:40.840 --> 51:43.196
From here you can see
all three kinds of rock.

51:44.920 --> 51:47.151
There, you see that layered section
across that slant?

51:47.280 --> 51:48.794
- <font color="#808080">KATZ:</font> Yeah.
- That's sedimentary.

51:51.040 --> 51:54.431
And the dark stuff here, pushing up
from underneath, that's igneous.

51:54.520 --> 51:55.670
Think volcanic.

51:56.120 --> 51:58.191
How do you know all this stuff?

51:58.360 --> 52:00.033
Well, there are these things called books.

52:00.640 --> 52:04.270
- Oh. No kidding, they're called books?
- Yeah, they're like TV for smart people.

52:05.200 --> 52:07.715
See, what we're talking about here,
Katz, is time.

52:08.520 --> 52:09.636
Geologic time.

52:10.040 --> 52:14.592
Hundreds of thousands of years
of enormous, shifting tectonic plates.

52:15.000 --> 52:17.913
It's like the world being reborn from below
while it's being eroded from above.

52:18.560 --> 52:19.960
Yeah. Well,

52:20.480 --> 52:22.676
when we get back I'm gonna buy you a TV.

52:23.840 --> 52:29.040
Because nobody gives a fuck
about shifting tectonic plates.

52:29.240 --> 52:30.230
Well, I do.

52:30.800 --> 52:32.029
You know why?

52:32.560 --> 52:35.075
Because I'm curious,
and I love being curious.

52:35.560 --> 52:37.916
I like knowing things about the world
that we're living in.

52:38.400 --> 52:40.631
Well, I think it's all fucking rock.

52:41.040 --> 52:42.360
Oh, yeah?

52:42.480 --> 52:44.676
I don't get bogged down in the minutiae.

52:44.960 --> 52:47.429
- I'm above the details.
- <font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLING)</font> You are?

52:47.640 --> 52:49.916
I'm big picture, Bryson.

52:50.080 --> 52:52.720
Oh. How's that working out for you?

52:52.800 --> 52:55.235
Ah, pretty, uh, fucking good.

53:01.400 --> 53:02.720
<font color="#D900D9">(HONKING)</font>

53:25.840 --> 53:26.956
Hello.

53:27.360 --> 53:28.635
We'd like a room, please.

53:28.920 --> 53:30.400
Two rooms.

53:31.040 --> 53:35.432
Oh, the Cubbies lost a double header,
and they're 11 games back.

53:35.800 --> 53:36.995
Don't act surprised.

53:38.480 --> 53:40.153
Tonight would be preferable.

53:42.320 --> 53:43.640
Hello there?

53:46.440 --> 53:48.432
Where are the Red Sox?

53:48.520 --> 53:49.954
Red Sox? Are you fucking kidding me? Whoa.

53:50.240 --> 53:51.356
Excuse me, ma'am.

53:51.440 --> 53:53.432
- Red Sox?
- I live in New England.

53:53.520 --> 53:57.150
Yeah, but Bryson, it's not about
where you live, it's about who you are.

53:57.400 --> 54:00.279
Oh, yeah? Well, I'm the kind of guy that
likes it when a team wins now and then.

54:00.440 --> 54:01.840
Well, you don't...

54:02.680 --> 54:06.071
You don't give up on a team just because
they've had a few bad years.

54:06.320 --> 54:08.312
<font color="#D900D9">(SCOFFING)</font>
A few bad years? Jesus.

54:08.520 --> 54:10.637
<font color="#808080">KATZ:</font> Baseball is about loyalty.

54:12.200 --> 54:15.113
Like, she knows what I'm talking about.
Don't you?

54:17.640 --> 54:19.074
Would you two like a minute?

54:20.000 --> 54:21.992
Hi, I'm Jeannie. How can I help y'all?

54:22.600 --> 54:24.432
Mother, let go of the man's hand.

54:25.960 --> 54:27.474
- Hi.
- Hi.

54:28.000 --> 54:30.196
Um, we'd like a couple of rooms. Please.

54:30.560 --> 54:32.597
Oh, sure. Where are you all from?

54:33.240 --> 54:36.551
Uh, I live in New Hampshire,
but I spent over 10 years in England.

54:36.680 --> 54:39.115
